    • Check into the Microtel

  • Full crew (DHS, MOB, KS, DS, mate)

      • 312 Talbot St, Ocean City, MD 21842

24 May

  • Scientific crew
    • Check out of Microtel
  • Full crew
    • 06:00 - 12:45: Recreational fishing survey aboard F/V Fin Chaser
  • Scientific crew
    • Return to Solomons, MD.

Packing list

🔲 3 fishing rods

🔲 Large cooler

🔲 Sampling bags and bag tags

🔲 Data sheets/clipboard

🔲 Two buckets

🔲 GPS

🔲 HOBO loggers (2)

🔲 MS222

🔲 Measuring board

🔲 Weight bucket with scales

🔲 >2 fish pots

Cruise plan

Times calculated at 12 knots.

23 May

  • 05:30: MOB, DHS, KS meet at Talbot St Pier, load gear onto F/V Fin Chaser
  • 06:00: Fin Chaser depart Talbot St Pier, transit to Great Eastern Reef
    • 38 25.8294, -74 46.062
  • 07:25: Arrive Great Eastern Reef.
    • Mate arranges gear for jigging.
    • Sci crew organizes MS-222 bucket
    • Environmental data recorded
  • 07:30: Mate begins jigging for 15 minutes.
    • All fish are weighed and measured.
    • First 10 black sea bass are sacrificed.
  • 07:45 Mate ends jigging.
  • 07:50: Survey crew begins drop survey.
    • 15 x 3 minute drops.
    • All fish are weighed and measured.
    • First 10 black sea bass are sacrificed.
  • 09:05: Drop survey ends. Transit to Twin Wrecks.
    • 38 13.8426, -74 45.4848
  • 10:05: Arrive Twin Wrecks.
  • 10:10: Mate begins jigging for 15 minutes. Data and specimen collection as above.
  • 10:20: Mate ends jigging.
  • 10:25: Survey crew begins drop survey, conducted as above.
  • 11:40: Drop survey ends. Return to Talbot St Pier.
  • 13:10: Arrive Talbot St Pier. Unload gear.

24 May

  • 05:30: MOB, DHS, KS meet at Talbot St Pier, load gear onto F/V Fin Chaser
  • 06:00: Fin Chaser depart Talbot St Pier, transit to M12
    • 38 16.1367, -74 41.0115
  • 07:45: Arrive M12.
    • Mate arranges gear for jigging.
    • Sci crew organizes MS-222 bucket
    • Environmental data recorded
  • 07:50: Mate begins jigging for 15 minutes.
    • All fish are weighed and measured.
    • First 10 black sea bass are sacrificed.
  • 08:05 Mate ends jigging.
  • 08:10: Survey crew begins drop survey.
    • 15 x 3 minute drops.
    • All fish are weighed and measured.
    • First 10 black sea bass are sacrificed.
  • 09:25: Drop survey ends. Transit to L12.
    • 38 16.1392, -74 41.9887
  • 09:30: Arrive L12.
  • 09:35: Mate begins jigging for 15 minutes. Data and specimen collection as above.
  • 09:45: Mate ends jigging.
  • 09:50: Survey crew begins drop survey, conducted as above.
  • 11:05: Drop survey ends. Return to Talbot St Pier.
  • 12:45: Arrive Talbot St Pier. Unload gear.
